screen_name: Good morning to everyone but nursing home management who fumbled the ball with COVID-19

My coworkers and boss who also tested positive all manifested differently, from asymptomatic to being hospitalized. This is a scary time and as more information comes out we need to be increasingly flexible and SMART. Also stop telling me I NEED to do FEES or I’m an awful slp.

That was the worst day. I was out of breath walking 10 feet (resp rate was ~18-27) and couldn’t breathe in the shower. My O2 sat never dropped below 95% (thankfully). I rode out 4 days of fever before I got tested. Gradually my breathing normalized and smell/taste returned.

Went I developed a fever- didn’t have a thermometer but I’m willing to bet ~100 F. The next day I spoke to a NP, explained I work with COVID+ pts at work he said “don’t get tested and ride it out” that day my fever spiked over 100.4 and my resting HR was 135. I cried a lot (2/?)

In case anyone wants to know: I was short of breath and had back pain for 1.5 weeks before I lost my sense of smell and taste (I was in a room with a pt who had a necrotic foot and colostomy and didn’t smell it-that’s what I panicked). The night my sense of taste and smell (1/?)
